A. Current Chain Map

BoundedLiveTrialAuthorization (authorization_id, carrier_id, strategy_family_id)
  │
  ▼
ExecutionIntent (id, authorization_id, signal_id)
  │  [execution_intents table — no strategy_family_id, no trial_binding_id]
  │
  ▼
OrderLifecycleService.create_order() → Order (ENTRY role)
  │  [orders table — signal_id only; no authorization_id, no execution_intent_id]
  │
  ▼
OrderStateMachine: CREATED → SUBMITTED → OPEN → PARTIALLY_FILLED → FILLED
  │  (Formal state machine with 9 states, transition guards, audit events)
  │
  ▼
PositionProjectionService.project_entry_fill() → Position
  │  [positions table — pos_{signal_id}; no governance IDs]
  │
  ▼
OrderManager.create_order_chain() → TP1..TP5 + SL orders
  │  [each Order has parent_order_id, oco_group_id, order_role]
  │
  ▼
OrderLifecycleService monitors TP/SL fills via WebSocket
  │
  ▼
PositionProjectionService.project_exit_fill() → realized_pnl + close
  │  [Exit outcome inferred from order_role + FILLED status — no ExitOutcome entity]
  │
  ▼
ReconciliationService.build_read_model() + periodic loop (300s)
  │  [keyed by symbol + order_id only; no governance IDs in findings]
  │
  ▼
BrcLiveLifecycleReviewRecord (append-only evidence)
  + ReviewLedger dict (mutable in-memory, not persisted as event chain)

Critical gap: The chain splits at the Order table. authorization_id is on ExecutionIntent and BrcLiveLifecycleReviewRecord, but NOT on Order or Position. The link between orders and intent is a reverse FK: execution_intents.order_id → orders.id. Orders cannot be queried forward from authorization.

